   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER FOUR GOD'S ECONOMY Scripture Reading: Col 3:10-11; 1:15-19; Eph 1:22-23; Rom 12:5; Eph 3:8-11, 2; 4:15-16; 1:10; 1 Tim 3:15-16; Rom 8:29; Heb 2:10-12; Matt 16:18-19; Rom 14:17; Heb 1:8; Rev 21:1-3; 22:1-2 OUTLINE Taking Christ as its centrality and universality Col 3:10-11.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Making Christ preeminent in all things Col 1:15-19: In the Godhead v. 15a.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>In the creation vv.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>15b-17.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>In the resurrection for the new creation, the church, the Body of Christ v. 18.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>In the fullness of the Godhead v. 19.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Producing the church to be: The Body of Christ Eph 1:22-23: The fullness of Him who fills all in all to be His expression.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>An organism constituted with His members Rom 12:5.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Built up: With the unsearchable riches of Christ through the divine dispensing Eph 3:8-11, 2.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>By the gifted members as the joints of the rich supply and by each one part operating in its measure Eph 4:16.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Through the growth in life of the Body, holding Christ as its Head Eph 4:15-16.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>For Christ to head up all things in Himself Eph 1:10.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The house of God 1 Tim 3:15-16: Composed of the many sons of God as the many brothers of Christ, the firstborn Son of God Rom 8:29; Heb 2:10-12.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The pillar and base of the truth.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The manifestation of God in the flesh the great mystery of godliness.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The kingdom of God Matt 16:18-19; Rom 14:17: For the divine administration.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>To express the divine authority Heb 1:8.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Consummating in the holy city, the New Jerusalem Rev 21 22.</S>
   </TEXT>
